CAVEAT on k. "#distinct r-balls <= #orbits" makes the count a LOWER bound, so k=1 here means "no two
vertices are distinguishable at the radii the patch supports", not "proven vertex-transitive". Local
homogeneity to radius r does not imply transitivity. The DISTINCTNESS direction is sound: two tilings
with disjoint ball-code sets are non-isomorphic, full stop.

CAVEAT on the fold test. It catches a vertex wrapped past 2pi, which covers overlap that lands vertex-on
-vertex (the position-keyed dedup merges them, inflating the angle sum). An overlap whose sheets are
misaligned would not be seen.

